<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/37682391-kristian-petersen"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1417911533i/37682391._UX100_CR0,1,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/37682391-kristian-petersen">Kristian Petersen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">He is self-aware of a fixation with prose, read any of his intros or discourses on his works for support. I am fine with this as his reaching for a pr<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">He is self-aware of a fixation with prose, read any of his intros or discourses on his works for support. I am fine with this as his reaching for a prosaic way to phrase things has the net effect of enriching one's vocabulary.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
