        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer725217522" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17197926899487781789">Soooo much better than the first trilogy and the ending is one of the best. I loved virtually everything about the series. I will never be a fan of the degree to which Donaldson luxuriates in the emotional issues of his characters, myes, I know that&apos;s part of building character depth, but there are limits. In this way, he&apos;s like a dog with a bone ... He won&apos;t let it lie.<br/><br/>But it&apos;s still one of my favorite settings and stories ever and well worth the read.</span>
  <span id="freeText17197926899487781789" style="display:none">Soooo much better than the first trilogy and the ending is one of the best. I loved virtually everything about the series. I will never be a fan of the degree to which Donaldson luxuriates in the emotional issues of his characters, myes, I know that's part of building character depth, but there are limits. In this way, he's like a dog with a bone ... He won't let it lie.<br /><br />But it's still one of my favorite settings and stories ever and well worth the read.</span>
